# Frontend Production Environment
These environment variables are used during production deployment to Vercel.

## Environment Variables

### VITE_API_BASE_URL
Set to: `https://timelyx-backend-1.onrender.com`

This points to the backend API running on Render. Update this URL if you change your Render deployment URL.

## Setting up in Vercel

1. Go to Vercel Dashboard → Your Project → Settings → Environment Variables
2. Add the following variable:
   - Key: `VITE_API_BASE_URL`
   - Value: `https://timelyx-backend-1.onrender.com`
   - Select Production environment

The .env.production file is used for local builds. For Vercel deployments, configure variables in the Vercel dashboard.
